{{Relic Infobox|Toy Box|2}}
{{R|Toy Box||2}} is a {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Ancient|Ancient|2}} {{2|Relics|Relic}}. Upon pickup, obtain 4 '''Wax Relics'''. Every 3 combats, your left-most '''Wax Relic''' will "melt" away, losing its effect. The '''Wax Relics''' are just recolored versions of regular (i.e. non-Shop, non-Event) {{2|Relics}} and have the same effect as the normal Relic besides going inactive after 3 combats.

== Sources ==
After fighting a {{2|Bosses|Boss}}, can be offered by {{KW|Tezcatara||2}}.

== Spawn Restrictions==
*Because '''Toy Box''' shares a relic pool with {{R|Pumpkin Candle||2}} and {{R|Golden Compass||2}}, only 1 of the 3 can be offered by {{KW|Tezcatara||2}}.

== Interactions ==
Upon picking up '''Toy Box''' you are presented with a selection of 4 {{2|Relics}}. They can not be skipped but the order in which you pick them up can be chosen, allowing you to put a less-valuable Relic or a Relic with an on-pickup effect as the left-most Relic.

=== Synergies ===
Some Relics have an on-pickup effect, meaning their bonus doesn't get reverted when the relic melts:
*{{R|Potion Belt||2}}
*{{R|Strawberry||2}}
*{{R|War Paint||2}}
*{{R|Whetstone||2}}
*{{R|Pear||2}}
*{{R|Mango||2}}
*{{R|Old Coin||2}}

== Notes ==
The game has an internal list of Relics, generated at the start of a run. '''Toy Box''' takes the next 4 Relics from the front of the list and turns them into Wax Relics, meaning it is not possible to gain a Wax Relic and its non-Wax counterpart in the same run. It also means you would encounter the same Relics anyways if you did not take '''Toy Box'''.
